				<h2>Zero crossing events with brushless DC motors</h2>
<p>I would like to ask a question about zero crossing event in a trapezoidal commutation on a brush-less DC motor. Here is a waveform that shows that the zero crossing event occurs every 180 electrical degrees in a sinusoidal commutation:<br> <img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/lcZrH.png" alt="sinusoidal"></p>

