<p>So as you see, the zero crossing occurs 30 electrical degrees after the previous commutation and 30 electrical degrees before the next commutation.
In a motor with one pole pair, we would have 30 electrical degrees = 30 mechanical degrees, so we would have this waveform: <img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/T5BCZ.png" alt="zero crossing">
